| Is the CD Becoming Obsolete?                                       |
|   from the fading-into-the-long-tail dept.                         |
|   posted by kdawson on Monday June 25, @23:02 (Media)              |
|   http://slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/06/26/011235               |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

mrnomas writes "What's to blame for the declining CD sales? Is it that
manufacturers are putting out more and more 'safe' (read: crap) music
while independent musicians are releasing online? Is it because iTunes is
now the third largest music retailer in the country? Or is it just that
[0]CDs are becoming obsolete?" Quoting: "Forbes.com [ran] an article
showing that [1]CD sales are expected to be down 20% in 2008 (slightly
higher than the 15% drop initially predicted). Why such a drop? What's
truly happening is a gradual shift away from physical media to
downloadable formats. What this indicates, so far, is that US sales of
digital music will be growing at an estimated rate of 28% in 2008,
however physical sales will drop even further, resulting in a net overall
decline.""

Discuss this story at:
    http://slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=07/06/26/011235

