| Giant Penguins Once Roamed Peru                                    |
|   from the not-cute-like-tux dept.                                 |
|   posted by kdawson on Tuesday June 26, @04:57 (It's funny.  Laugh.|
|   http://linux.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/06/26/0126244        |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

[0]Spielas Roberts points out as "obvious Linux fodder" the coverage of a
study just published in PNAS claiming that, on fossil evidence, [1]giant
penguins once stalked the plains of Peru. One species goes back over 40
million years and its members were as large as modern king penguins. They
were warm adapted. Members of another species, 30 million years ago,
stood 5 feet high and made their living spearfishing with their 1-foot
beaks. Here's an [2]artist's impression.

