| OpenSuSE to Release Linux Distro for Educators                     |
|   from the not-the-best-conglomerate-word-ever dept.               |
|   posted by Zonk on Tuesday June 26, @09:00 (Education)            |
|   http://linux.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/06/26/1225220        |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

[0]christian.einfeldt writes "The next version of openSUSE, due out in
the fall, [1]will include an add-on CD optimized for educators. According
to the Education section of the openSUSE wiki, the openSUSE community
sees the add-on as a way to make it easy for school administrators to
create both networked systems and stand-alone desktops for teachers and
students. To tailor the add-on CD to the needs of educators, the openSUSE
community is asking educators and technologists to submit their software
successes, applications used, and 'HOW-TOs' for writing applications and
using applications. Dubbed the SLEDucator, the package collection is
being included as an add-on, as opposed to a new distro or a fork."

