+--------------------------------------------------------------------+
| NY Legislature Rejects "Microsoft Amendment"                       |
|   from the joy-in-mudville dept.                                   |
|   posted by kdawson on Tuesday June 26, @17:50 (Slashback)         |
|   http://politics.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/06/26/2112208     |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

An anonymous reader writes "Finally, some good news on electronic voting.
The New York state legislature [0] rejected an amendment proposed by
Microsoft's lobbyists which would have [1]gutted New York's requirements
for voting machine vendors to turn over their source code to the state
Board of Elections. Assemblywoman Barbara Lifton commented: 'The voting
machine vendors have known for two years what our laws said. Now they're
saying that those parts of their systems using Microsoft software have to
be proprietary? It's just wrong.'"

